An Act relative to a first-time homebuyer tax deduction.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 1. As used in this section, the following words shall, unless the context clearly
2 requires otherwise, have the following meanings:
3 “Closing Cost,” any expenses associated with a mortgage beyond the down payment,
4 including appraisal fees, mortgage generation fees, bank fees, mortgage generation fees, bank
5 fees, recording fees, inspection fees, attorney fees and escrow fees.
6 “First-time homebuyer,” a Massachusetts resident who has not owned a home at any
7 point in the last three years.
8 Section 2: Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary there shall be a
9 deduction associated with first time homebuyers valued at the cost of any additional closing costs
10 accrued through the homebuying process.
